    "/v2/activeUsers": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "ActiveUserControllerV2_getUsersV2",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "start",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "end",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "tenantId",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "filter",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "fields",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "array",
                  "items": {
                    "type": "object"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "summary": "Returns active users from the cache within the given time range, with\noptional server-side filtering and field projection.\n\n**`filter`** — a [`filtrex`](https://github.com/cshaa/filtrex) expression\nevaluated against each mapped user. Strings must be **double-quoted**.\n\n| Goal | Expression |\n|---|---|\n| Single country | `country == \"Germany\"` |\n| Exclude guests | `roles != \"guest\"` |\n| Platform filter | `platform == \"desktop\"` |\n| Compound condition | `country == \"USA\" and browser == \"Chrome\"` |\n| Multiple devices | `device in (\"mobile\", \"tablet\")` |\n\n**`fields`** — comma-separated top-level fields to return from the mapped\nuser. Valid values: `id`, `roles`, `country`, `sessionId`, `language`,\n`platform`, `browser`, `device`, `domain`.\nWhen omitted, all top-level fields are returned.\n\n| Goal | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Identity only | `id,sessionId` |\n| Location and browser | `id,country,browser,platform` |\n| Full user (default) | _(omit param)_ |",
        "tags": [
          "ActiveUserControllerV2"
        ]
      }
    },
    "/v2/events": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "EventsControllerV2_getEventsV2",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "start",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "end",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "tenantId",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "filter",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "fields",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "dataFields",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "array",
                  "items": {
                    "type": "object"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "summary": "Returns events from the cache within the given time range, with optional\nserver-side filtering and field projection.\n\n**`filter`** — a [`filtrex`](https://github.com/cshaa/filtrex) expression\nevaluated against each mapped event (`name`, `date`, `data`, `identifyId`,\n`sessionId`). Strings must be **double-quoted**.\n\n| Goal | Expression |\n|---|---|\n| Single event type | `name == \"buttonClick\"` |\n| Exclude an event type | `name != \"pageView\"` |\n| Compound condition | `name == \"formSubmit\" and sessionId == \"abc123\"` |\n| Multiple allowed names | `name in (\"click\", \"hover\", \"focus\")` |\n\n**`fields`** — comma-separated top-level fields to return from the mapped\nevent. Valid values: `name`, `date`, `data`, `identifyId`, `sessionId`.\nWhen omitted, all top-level fields are returned.\n\n| Goal | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Name and date only | `name,date` |\n| Include identity info | `name,date,identifyId,sessionId` |\n| Full event (default) | _(omit param)_ |\n\n**`dataFields`** — comma-separated dot-notation paths to project from\n`event.data`. When omitted, the full `data` object is returned.\n\n| Goal | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Single top-level key | `widgetName` |\n| Nested key (flat output) | `attributes.size` |\n| Multiple keys | `widgetName,attributes.size,user.id` |\n| Full data payload (default) | _(omit param)_ |",
        "tags": [
          "EventsControllerV2"
        ]
      }
    },
    "/v2/customEvents": {
      "get": {
        "operationId": "EventsControllerV2_getCustomerEventsV2",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "start",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "end",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "tenantId",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "filter",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "fields",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "dataFields",
            "required": true,
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "array",
                  "items": {
                    "type": "object"
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "summary": "Returns only customer-defined custom events (name prefix `customEvent*`)\nfrom the cache within the given time range. The `data` field always\nconforms to {@link CustomerCustomEventAttributes} (`action_type`, `category`,\n`label`, `metadata`).\n\nThis is a pre-filtered view of `v2/events` — only events whose `name`\nstarts with `customEvent` are included before any additional filtering\nor projection is applied.\n\n**`filter`** — a [`filtrex`](https://github.com/cshaa/filtrex) expression\nevaluated against each mapped event. Reference top-level fields or\nknown `data` sub-fields. Strings must be **double-quoted**.\n\n| Goal | Expression |\n|---|---|\n| Specific event name | `name == \"customEventButtonClick\"` |\n| By action type | `name == \"customEventTrack\"` |\n| Exclude a name | `name != \"customEventPageLoad\"` |\n| Multiple names | `name in (\"customEventClick\", \"customEventHover\")` |\n\n**`dataFields`** — comma-separated dot-notation paths to project from\n`event.data`. Valid values: `action_type`, `category`, `label`,\n`metadata`, or nested paths inside `metadata` (e.g. `metadata.size`).\nWhen omitted, the full `data` object is returned.\n\n| Goal | Value |\n|---|---|\n| Category and label only | `category,label` |\n| Action and nested metadata | `action_type,metadata.size` |\n| Full data payload (default) | _(omit param)_ |",
        "tags": [
          "EventsControllerV2"
        ]
      }
    },
